<b>This is how the song works: - </b>1/8/02 7:08:58 PM<br>~ <b>Kasreyn Giantharrow</b><blockquote>It's a ranged pillar-type AE effect.  It affects as many as 4 mobs, plus the bard.   Unless it's changed since I tested it, trust a bard who sang it with 15 mobs in his immediate vicinity - and hit 4 of them, plus himself.  It does hit the target and in the case it didn't appear to, I suspect the message would have appeared just after you died.  It also hits up to 3 more mobs if they're close enough, as well as the caster, and is identical, except being crippled, to the ranged AE capabilities of druids and wizards.  Marginally useful for finishing up a dual charmkite or after tagging the next in a serial dotkite, or for really pissing off the enchanter in an average dungeon group.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
